Senator Shehu Sani, representing the Senatorial District which encompasses Kajuru, has dismissed reports of killings in Kaduna State; the Senator revealed that when he inquired he was told that it was an old incident that the governor went to dig up.
Senator Sani stated “What the people of the area told me was that the issue happened since Sunday and the security agencies waded in and resolved it immediately. There was no tension that can threaten peace in the area.”
Sani, then said that he wondered why the Governor decided to bring up the matter a day to the election, warning that the people will not be distracted.







			
